\subsection{Transfer Learning Strategy}

A \textbf{two-stage fine-tuning} approach was employed to balance feature reuse from ImageNet with domain adaptation to Indian street food images.

\subsubsection{Stage 1 — Classifier-Only Training}

All convolutional (feature extraction) layers were \textbf{frozen}, and only the newly added classifier head was trained. This allows the randomly initialised classifier to converge using the stable, high-quality features from ImageNet, without corrupting the pre-trained convolutional weights.

\begin{lstlisting}[caption={Stage 1: Freeze backbone, train classifier only}]
model = models.mobilenet_v2(pretrained=True)

# Freeze all convolutional layers
for param in model.parameters():
    param.requires_grad = False

# Replace classifier head: 1280 -> 12 classes
model.classifier[1] = nn.Linear(model.last_channel, 12)

# Only classifier parameters are trainable
for param in model.classifier.parameters():
    param.requires_grad = True

optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)
\end{lstlisting}

\subsubsection{Stage 2 — Partial Unfreezing (Gradual Fine-Tuning)}

After the classifier converged (10 epochs), the \textbf{last 3 convolutional blocks} (\texttt{features[-3:]}) were unfrozen with a \textbf{reduced learning rate} ($10^{-4}$) to allow the deeper layers to adapt to food-specific features while avoiding catastrophic forgetting of the general-purpose ImageNet representations.

\begin{lstlisting}[caption={Stage 2: Unfreeze last 3 blocks for fine-tuning}]
for param in model.features[-3:].parameters():
    param.requires_grad = True

optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=1e-4)
\end{lstlisting}

This two-stage strategy is a well-established transfer learning technique: the frozen-backbone stage prevents the randomly initialised classifier from sending noisy gradients through the pre-trained features, while the subsequent partial unfreezing allows domain-specific adaptation in the higher convolutional layers.

\subsection{Inference Transform}

At inference time, images are pre-processed with a deterministic pipeline (no augmentation):

\begin{lstlisting}[caption={Inference pre-processing pipeline (model\_inference.py)}]
transform = transforms.Compose([
    transforms.Resize((224, 224)),
    transforms.ToTensor(),
    # Note: ImageNet normalisation can be added here for improved accuracy
])
\end{lstlisting}

Softmax is applied over the 12 logits to obtain class probabilities, and \texttt{torch.max} selects the predicted class and its confidence score.

