\subsection{Architecture}

The Streamlit app follows a clean single-file layout. The model is loaded once at startup using \texttt{@st.cache\_resource} to avoid redundant disk reads across interactions.

\subsection{UI Layout}

The app uses a \textbf{two-column layout}: the left column shows the uploaded image, and the right column streams the prediction results, progress bar, and metadata.

\begin{lstlisting}[caption={Two-column prediction display (app.py)}]
col1, col2 = st.columns(2)

with col1:
    st.image(image, caption="Uploaded Image", use_container_width=True)

with col2:
    pred, conf = predict(image, model)
    st.subheader(f"Predicted: {pred.replace('_', ' ').title()}")
    st.progress(int(conf * 100))
    st.write(f"Confidence: {conf*100:.2f}%")
\end{lstlisting}

